Sir Harry Warden Stanley Chilcott , also known as Warden Chilcott, was Conservative MP for Liverpool Walton.
He was elected with the backing of the Coalition government in 1918, was returned unopposed in 1922 and 1923, was elected again in 1924, and stood down in 1929.
